All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, Function<T,T>
public class Print<T>
extends AbstractFunction<T,T>

The Print-Function prints arguments to a specified print stream and returns them. If no print stream is specified, the standard out is taken as default. Print-Functions can be used to log a composition of functions at a specified level. To do so just a Print-Function has to be inserted at the right place like 

   Function<Number, Double> tan = Functions.compose(div, Functions.compose(new Print<Double>(), sin), cos);
instead of 
   Function<Number, Double> tan = Functions.compose(div, sin, cos);
